# Conda Environment

This project uses the `triton` conda environment. Before running Python scripts, tests, benchmarks, or other commands that depend on project dependencies (torch, triton, etc.), activate it:

```bash
conda activate triton
```

When using the Shell tool, prefix commands with conda activation and the local Triton source path:

```bash
source "$(conda info --base)/etc/profile.d/conda.sh" && conda activate triton && PYTHONPATH=/root/triton_workspace/triton/python <your command>
```

If a command fails with `ModuleNotFoundError` (e.g. missing `torch`), retry after activating the `triton` environment.
